## Features

### Info Panel
Live system information displayed at launch — click any field to act on it directly.

| Field | Click Action |
|---|---|
| COMPUTER | Rename machine |
| USER | Change password |
| WINDOWS | Enter product key / activate |
| DOMAIN | Join or leave domain |
| NETWORK | Open network manager |
| UPTIME | Restart or shut down |

---

### Total Deploy
Guided full setup sequence for new machines. Walks through:
1. Rename computer
2. Create local account
3. Join domain *(rename and join are applied atomically — no stale name in AD)*
4. Activate Windows
5. Vendor Purge
6. System Sanitize
7. Install apps
8. Add printer *(optional)*

---

### System Sanitize
Removes Microsoft bloat and applies essential tweaks in one pass.

**Bloat removal** strips: Teams, Clipchamp, Xbox, Cortana, News, Weather, Maps, People, Feedback Hub, Your Phone, To Do, Office Hub, ZuneMusic/Video, Messaging, OneConnect.

**Essential tweaks** apply:
- Telemetry and DiagTrack service disabled
- Bing and Cortana removed from Start Menu search
- Taskbar cleaned (Meet Now, People, Task View, Widgets, Copilot removed)
- File extensions shown by default
- Item checkboxes disabled in Explorer
- Hibernation disabled
- Windows Update active hours set to 8am–5pm
- Windows 10 right-click context menu restored
- Startup Run keys cleared
- Edge startup boost and background mode disabled
- OneDrive, Teams, Copilot autostart blocked via policy
- Timezone set to New Zealand Standard Time
- Explorer restarted to apply visual changes

---

### Vendor Purge
Auto-detects the machine manufacturer and removes vendor-specific bloatware.

**Supported vendors:** HP, Dell, Lenovo, Acer, ASUS, MSI, Toshiba, Samsung, Microsoft Surface

HP machines additionally run a WMI-based removal pass targeting HP Wolf Security and HP Sure Sense.

---

### Application Provisioning
Checkbox-based app installer powered by Winget.

**Critical (ticked by default):** Microsoft 365, Chrome, Firefox, Google Drive, VLC, 7-Zip, Adobe Acrobat Reader

**Optional:** LocalSend, CrystalDiskInfo, Angry IP Scanner, Everything, HP Support Assistant, Malwarebytes, Winaero Tweaker, O&O ShutUp10, PowerToys, Process Explorer, Bulk Crap Uninstaller, Autoruns, K-Lite Codec Pack

**Extras:** Set Chrome as default browser, Set VLC as default media player, Update all installed applications

Firefox installs with **uBlock Origin** pre-deployed to the distribution extensions folder — activates automatically on first launch.

---

### Network Manager
- View all active adapters with IP, subnet, gateway and DNS
- Apply static IP configuration per adapter
- Switch adapter back to DHCP
- Open Network Connections (ncpa.cpl)

---

### Domain Tools
- Join / Leave domain
- Generate Group Policy report (saves HTML to Desktop)
- Force `gpupdate /force`
- Flush DNS and re-register
- View `dsregcmd /status` output
- Leave Azure AD join

---

### User Provisioning
Create local accounts with username, full name, password and admin/standard group selection. Includes a shortcut to `lusrmgr.msc` for full user management.

---

### Printer Setup
Add network printers by IP with protocol selection (RAW/LPR/IPP/WSD). Supports driver installation from a local `.inf` file or a UNC network share path.

---

### System Diagnostics
- Battery report (HTML, opens automatically)
- Energy efficiency report
- System file health check (DISM + SFC)
- Memory diagnostic (schedules on next boot)
- Disk health report (SMART status, saves to Desktop)
- Driver Verifier (advanced)
- Hardware info dump — CPU, RAM, GPU (saves to Desktop)
- Windows Update repair — resets services, clears cache, re-registers DLLs, triggers scan

---

## QuickSanitize (Headless)

`QuickSanitize.ps1` runs the full Bloat Removal + Vendor Purge + Essential Tweaks sequence with no UI — pure console output, suitable for running remotely or via a login script.

```powershell
# Run as Administrator
.\QuickSanitize.ps1
```

---

## Customisation

| What to change | Where |
|---|---|
| Default Windows product key | Search `DEFAULT KEY` in the script |
| App install list | `AP-Check` entries in `Show-AppPicker` |
| Vendor bloat lists | `$vendorBloat` and `$vendorWinget` hashtables in `Run-VendorPurge` |
| Timezone | `Set-TimeZone -Id` in `Run-EssentialTweaks` |
| Update active hours | `ActiveHoursStart` / `ActiveHoursEnd` in `Run-EssentialTweaks` |
| Startup banner text | `$bannerLines` array |

---

## Notes

- Some AppX packages (Xbox, People) may fail to remove on education or managed builds — these errors are non-fatal and can be ignored
- The Windows 10 right-click menu restore requires an Explorer restart to take effect — this happens automatically
- Domain join with simultaneous rename uses `Add-Computer -NewName` to ensure Active Directory receives the correct name immediately
- uBlock Origin is deployed via the Firefox distribution extensions folder — the URL points to a specific version and may need updating periodically

